---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import BlogLatestPosts from '~/components/widgets/BlogLatestPosts.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'SNN Lab',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <main class="flex flex-col min-h-screen">
    <section class="relative px-[5vw] py-[clamp(3rem,8vh,6rem)] m-auto max-w-6xl text-center md:text-left">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-[clamp(1.875rem,5vw,3rem)] font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-tighter mb-4 font-heading">
          Social Networks & Neuroscience Lab (SNN Lab)
        </h1>
        <p class="text-[clamp(1.1rem,2vw,1.25rem)] font-semibold text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
          Department of Sociology, Yonsei University | PI: Yoosik Youm
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-muted dark:text-slate-300">
        <p class="mb-10 text-[clamp(1.125rem,1.5vw,1.35rem)] leading-[1.6] text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
          At the SNN Lab, we explore the intricate web connecting <span class="font-bold"
            >social networks, the human brain, and health outcomes.</span
          >
          Our research is driven by three fundamental inquiries:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-none grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-[clamp(1.5rem,4vw,3rem)] mb-12 p-0">
          <li class="flex flex-col group">
            <div
              class="w-full aspect-video bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl mb-4 overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-700"
            >
              <img
                src="/c1.png"
                alt="Social Basis of the Brain"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
              />
            </div>
            <span class="font-bold text-black dark:text-white text-lg mb-2"> The Social Basis of the Brain </span>
            <span class="text-[clamp(0.9rem,1vw,1rem)] leading-relaxed">
              Investigating how our surrounding social structures and interactions physically shape and change the human
              brain.
            </span>
          </li>

          <li class="flex flex-col group">
            <div
              class="w-full aspect-video bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl mb-4 overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-700"
            >
              <img
                src="/c2.png"
                alt="Neural Basis of the Social"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
              />
            </div>
            <span class="font-bold text-black dark:text-white text-lg mb-2"> The Neural Basis of the Social </span>
            <span class="text-[clamp(0.9rem,1vw,1rem)] leading-relaxed">
              Decoding the neurological mechanisms that allow human beings to navigate and maintain complex social
              networks.
            </span>
          </li>

          <li class="flex flex-col group">
            <div
              class="w-full aspect-video bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl mb-4 overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center border border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-700"
            >
              <img
                src="/c3.png"
                alt="Behavioral and Health Implications"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
              />
            </div>
            <span class="font-bold text-black dark:text-white text-lg mb-2"> Behavioral & Health Implications </span>
            <span class="text-[clamp(0.9rem,1vw,1rem)] leading-relaxed">
              Analyzing the interactive role of networks and neurology in determining individual behavior and long-term
              health.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-[clamp(1rem,1.2vw,1.125rem)] leading-[1.7]">
          Our work is grounded in lab-directed longitudinal studies, including
          <a
            href="/projects/kshappro"
            class="font-bold hover:text-primary transition-colors underline decoration-dotted underline-offset-4"
            >KSHAP (Korean Social Life, Health, and Aging Project)</a
          >,
          <a
            href="/projects/ksahpro"
            class="font-bold hover:text-primary transition-colors underline decoration-dotted underline-offset-4"
            >KSAH (Korean Study of Adolescent Health)</a
          >, and
          <a
            href="/projects/kcwispro"
            class="font-bold hover:text-primary transition-colors underline decoration-dotted underline-offset-4"
            >KCWIS (Korean Child Wellbeing Index Survey)</a
          >. By integrating Social Network Analysis (SNA), Neuroimaging, and Machine Learning, we translate complex
          interdisciplinary data into insights for a healthier society.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="relative px-[5vw] py-12 m-auto max-w-7xl">
      <div class="text-center pb-10 md:pb-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-muted dark:text-slate-400 text-[clamp(1.1rem,1.5vw,1.25rem)]">
          A sample of our actual collected network in the Korean Study of Adolescent Health (Cohort 2022).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="network-viz-container">
        <iframe
          src="/ksah_indigo_wave7.html"
          title="Network Animation"
          width="100%"
          height="650px"
          style="border: 0; overflow: hidden;"
          allowtransparency="true"
          class="network-iframe"></iframe>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="bg-[#D9EAFD] dark:bg-black">
      <BlogLatestPosts title="Recent Lab News" classes={{ container: 'py-4 md:py-4 lg:py-4' }} />
    </div>

    <style>
      .network-viz-container {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        background: #f8fafc;
        border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        border-radius: 12px;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .network-iframe {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: 450px;
        /* Allows clicks on buttons */
        pointer-events: auto;

        /* 'touch-action: pan-y' allows the user to scroll the whole PAGE up and down,
       but prevents the IFRAME from capturing the scroll/pinch to zoom.
    */
        touch-action: pan-y;
      }
    </style>
  </main></Layout
>
